---

<section class="py-24">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Section header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-text">
        Frequently asked questions
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-text-secondary text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Need help with something? Check this list first, and maybe you'll find what you're looking for.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <!-- Q1 -->
      <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-text mb-3">
          How do I install the alt:V Multiplayer Client?
        </h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Go to our download page, download the installer and run it, it will guide you through the installation process.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Q2 -->
      <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-text mb-3">
          Is alt:V free to use?
        </h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Yes, it is completely free to use. However, you need to own a copy of Grand Theft Auto V to play.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Q3 -->
      <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-text mb-3">
          Will I get banned from GTA Online if I use alt:V?
        </h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
          alt:V does not connect to Rockstar services and does not make any changes to your game files.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Q4 -->
      <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-text mb-3">
          What are the system requirements?
        </h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
          They are the same as those for Grand Theft Auto V. You can find them on the official website of the game.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Q5 -->
      <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-text mb-3">
          Which version of GTA V is supported?
        </h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
          alt:V Multiplayer supports all legal distributions of GTA V, whether downloaded via Rockstar Launcher, Steam, or Epic Games.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Q6 -->
      <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-text mb-3">
          How can I support the team behind alt:V?
        </h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
          You can contribute directly to open-source projects on GitHub or ask on our Discord.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
